  • Package com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message

    • Class com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message.HttpBaseMessage extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • cmdReturnChannelURI

          URI cmdReturnChannelURI
          The return channel for all commmands. Specify the channel name that you want return status to be sent. This channel should be unique for your usage.

        • connectionId

          long connectionId
          When a setup command is sent to the module, it will create a connectionId and return it on the return channel. This connectionId needs to be specified for all subsequent commands (eg, data messages HttpDataMessage and teardown messages HttpTeardownMessage

        • status

          HttpBaseMessage.HTTP_BRIDGE_STATUS status
          The status of the command. This value is set and returned for each command on the return channel. See HTTP_BRIDGE_STATUS values for more info.

    • Class com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message.HttpDataMessage extends HttpBaseMessage implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • inputHttpChannelURI

          URI inputHttpChannelURI
          (optional) The URI for the http input channel. Any input data required for the specified Http request is sent on this channel. The module will read the data from this channel and send it to the Http output stream for the Http request. For example any form data would be published on this channel.

        • inputTimeoutSeconds

          long inputTimeoutSeconds
          (optional) Timeout value for the inputHttpChannelURI. This value specifies how many seconds the module will wait for data on the inputHttpChennelURI for the specified Http request. If the timeout expires, the module will no longer wait for input data and continue with the request. Default value is 30 seconds.

        • outputHttpChannelURI

          URI outputHttpChannelURI
          (optional) The output channel URI where any output from the Http request is sent. If the Http request has any data on its input stream, it will be published to this channel.

        • urlPath

          String urlPath
          (optional) Path information that is appended to the HttpSetupMessage.connectionUrl for this command. For example, if the connectionURL is http://myserver.com, this urlPath could be "/api/getName?id=1" creating a complete URL of: http://myserver.com/api/getName?id=1.

        • httpRequest

          String httpRequest
          (Required) The actual Http request. No restrictions on this, the string is sent directly to the Http server. Typical values are GET, PUT, POST, DELETE, HEAD.

        • requestHeaders

          Map<K,V> requestHeaders
          (optional) Specify the Http request headers in the Map. The format is name value pairs. Example: "Content-Language", "en-US". These values are sent directly to the Http request.

        • useCache

          boolean useCache
          (required) Specify whether you want the Http request to use any cached values. True means it is ok to used cached values. False means do not use cached data. Default is false;

        • responseHeaders

          Map<K,V> responseHeaders
          These headers are returned from the Http request. The number of headers and values depends on the Http request.

        • responseCode

          int responseCode
          The response code returned from the Http request.

        • responseMessage

          String responseMessage
          The response message returned from the Http Request.

    • Class com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message.HttpSetupMessage extends HttpBaseMessage implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • connectionUrl

          URL connectionUrl
          The URL for the Http request. For example: http://myServer.com. This field is required.

        • proxyHost

          String proxyHost
          (optional) The Proxy host if needed. If the proxy is specified, it is used with the proxyPort to setup a proxy for the Http request. If no proxy is needed, leave this empty.

        • proxyPort

          int proxyPort
          (optional) The proxy port if the proxy host is specified.

        • dataCmdChannelURI

          URI dataCmdChannelURI
          A data command channel URI is returned from the setup command. This channel name is unique for this connection. Use this channel to send your Data messages to the module.

        • dataCmdReturnChannelURI

          URI dataCmdReturnChannelURI
          A data command return channel URI is returned from the setup command. This channel receives status for any data messages.

    • Class com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message.HttpTeardownMessage extends HttpBaseMessage implements Serializable
